name: Ed's Jazz Concert(ina) NEW
description: - All proceeds go towards funding the University of Brighton Graphic Design and Illustration summer degree show 2013 - A beautiful 3 colour silkscreened concertina of a fiery hard bop session, by Ed Cheverton. Have a look at his website here for more colourful explorations of collage, cartoon and composition : cargocollective.com/edwardcheverton 50p postage to the UK or free delivery to the Brighton area via my green bike. Will deliver internationally so please get in touch to find out how much it will be. Find out more about our eclectic course here: www.gdi-brighton.co.uk

name: Sam's Cube
description: - All proceeds go towards funding the University of Brighton Graphic Design and Illustration summer degree show 2013 - The Designer Eternal optimist Sam Quinton’s favourite thing to do is put an idea into practise. He likes all of his projects to have an underlying concept, and if it can make people smile then that’s an extra 10 points. He’s a big fan of heavy music, astronomy and biscuits. samquinton.tumblr.com Hand screenprinted by our friend Martyn at Links T Shirts in Brighton, onto super-premium Fruit of The Looms, which are 100% cotton. There have been 13 of these fine T shirts printed, and there will only ever be 13 in existence. We are the class of '13. It's our lucky number. All of the proceeds from this here shop go to help fund our end of degree show which will take place next year in London - and you never know, you may just get something special thrown in with your order (but you didn't hear that from me). 50p postage/free hand delivery if within Brighton. Find out more about our eclectic course here: www.gdi-brighton.co.uk

name: Chris' Cat
description: - All proceeds go towards funding the University of Brighton Graphic Design and Illustration summer degree show 2013 - SOLD OUT - Now only available from the Lik + Neon shop off of Brick lane. More info: likneon.com The Designer Chris Harnan is all about mixed media work and experimentation. He tries to communicate the energy with which his work is made and is a fan of flukes and mistakes. Pencil scribbles, finger painting and found materials prit sticked to a page of some unknown material, Chris is almost, but not quite, a small child. He understands if people were to think that though, and he is ok with it. chrisharnan.tumblr.com Hand screenprinted by our friend Martyn at Links T Shirts in Brighton, onto super-premium Fruit of The Looms, which are 100% cotton. name: Rory's A
description: - All proceeds go towards funding the University of Brighton Graphic Design and Illustration summer degree show 2013 - The Designer Rory Cahill is a Manchester born and bred designer whose work ranges from image making to graphic design and art direction. His love of process and the simple joy of craft, combined with a keen aesthetic eye, results in bold experimental images that convey a sense of play. Clients and collaborations include OWT Creative, Cut & Paste Festival and Pop Deviant. Rory enjoys fresh air, good food and the occasional whisky sour. cargocollective.com/whoisrorycahill Hand screenprinted by our friend Martyn at Links T Shirts in Brighton, onto super-premium Fruit of The Looms, which are 100% cotton.
